{
  "stem": "26465.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Except I know-- I knew there was something terrible going to-- something terrible was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the moment, I stood there alone-- aside from others-- and I felt almost like a premonition that a chapter of my life is finished and another is going to start-- something is going to happen, something terrible.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it did, of course, very shortly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But before that, before that I was-- I was sent to-- I was really volunteering to go to [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Chevarisk. ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Chevarisk ?] is a city-- not too big a city, but a city where they make a lot of sugar from the beets-- sugar beets.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And apparently, the sugar factory, or a sugar place, was bombard-- bombarded.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And all the sugar went out in the open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And people were running from all sides to pick up this sugar in the bags-- as much as they could.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I volunteered to go there with my-- my friend, Helen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we brought, believe me, about 20 pounds of sugar each, and braving-- braving the shooting and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because it was quite a distance-- it was like here to [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kitchener ?] to walk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we slept in a-- in a barn over the night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And finally, when we came home with the sugar, we were really heroines-- we were somebody.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And that was one of the pre-war incidents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "How did things change when Germany invaded?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things have changed in that way-- first of all, there were changes in my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Both of my aunts got married.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle was married, as well, just a year before the war, had his wife paralyzed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My uncle, a new uncle that came into the house, took over.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
